Economic Freedom Fighters leader Julius Malema has dismissed allegations that the EFF pressured the police to arrest Operation Dudula Movement leader Nhlanhla ‘Lux’ Dlamini. Members of the Dudula Movement had allegedly ransacked Victor Ramerafe’s property following a tip-off from the community that drugs were allegedly being sold from Ramerafe’s home. Malema says Ramerafe, who felt unsafe, asked EFF members to accompany him to the Police Station to lay a complaint against the Dudula Movement. MALEMA: The poor man asked us to accompany him to open a case. The EFF did not open a case against Nhlanhla Lux, we just accompanied our member who told us that he doesn’t feel safe. #MalemaOnMotswedingFM — Economic Freedom Fighters (@EFFSouthAfrica) March 27, 2022   Dlamini was arrested on Friday and faces charges of malicious damage to property, theft, and burglary. His bail application is expected to take place on Monday. Malema says his party members will continue to support the vulnerable. Operation Dudula members say Nhlanhla Dlamini’s arrest politically motivated: 